menu "VMMU — Software Memory Management Unit"

config VMMU_MAX_IPC_SIZE
    int "Maximum size in bytes for a single app<->kernel IPC copy"
    default 512
    help
      Size of the static staging buffer used by copy_from_app and
      copy_to_app. Any IPC transfer larger than this is rejected.
      Must be a power of two. Increase if your app messages are large,
      but keep in mind this is permanently allocated in BSS.

config VMMU_FRAME_POOL_SIZE
    int "Number of frames in the physical frame pool"
    default 64
    help
      Total number of 4KB frames available for app heap allocation.
      On the Nucleo F429ZI (256KB SRAM) with kernel overhead, 48-64
      frames is a realistic maximum.

endmenu
